wifi: mt76: mt7925: disable runtime PM and deep sleep for MT7927

MT7927 firmware MCU locks up after extended operation when runtime PM
or deep sleep is enabled. The driver cannot recover because mac_reset
is not yet supported for MT7927 (CLR_OWN destroys DMA ring config).

Disable runtime PM and deep sleep for MT7927 until a working recovery
path is in place. MT7925 behavior is unchanged.

Signed-off-by: Javier Tia <floss@jetm.me>

diff --git a/mt7925/init.c b/mt7925/init.c
index 84af52a..e3b6f01 100644
--- a/mt7925/init.c
+++ b/mt7925/init.c
@@ -245,3 +245,3 @@ int mt7925_register_device(struct mt792x_dev *dev)
-	if (!mt76_is_usb(&dev->mt76)) {
+	if (!mt76_is_usb(&dev->mt76) && !is_mt7927(&dev->mt76)) {
 		dev->pm.enable_user = true;
 		dev->pm.enable = true;
